The paper discusses a method for improving the performance of context-aware recommender systems using a Gaussian Process Latent Variable Model Factorization. This involves utilizing non-linear dimensionality reduction and applying an appropriate prior to the original GP model. The paper falls under the categories of machine learning (cs.LG), information retrieval (cs.IR), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), social and information networks (cs.SI), and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
